1
00:00:37,203 --> 00:00:38,996
EPISODE 8

2
00:00:42,542 --> 00:00:45,920
- So, was the operation a success?
- I'd say so.

3
00:00:46,546 --> 00:00:48,422
We blew up the drugs,
just like we planned.

4
00:00:48,506 --> 00:00:51,717
And we secured samples
as well as video evidence.

5
00:00:51,801 --> 00:00:53,844
So, yeah, it was a success.

6
00:00:53,928 --> 00:00:54,971
Oh, but one thing.

7
00:00:55,555 --> 00:00:56,931
Where the hell did Bulgae come from?

8
00:00:57,014 --> 00:00:59,350
Jeong Ho-myeong, you got any ideas?

9
00:00:59,433 --> 00:01:02,353
That van showed up
right when Bulgae appeared.

10
00:01:02,436 --> 00:01:03,771
This is no coincidence.

11
00:01:03,854 --> 00:01:06,524
I don't know what it is,
but they were after something.

12
00:01:09,569 --> 00:01:11,362
- Oh, right! That van.
- What the hell?

13
00:01:12,363 --> 00:01:13,864
- Geez.
- The van from earlier.

14
00:01:13,948 --> 00:01:16,367
It's the same van I saw
at Kim Seon-jung's house the other day.

15
00:01:17,743 --> 00:01:18,744
Let me see.

16
00:01:20,288 --> 00:01:21,664
You're right. That's the one.

17
00:01:22,331 --> 00:01:23,874
Hey, did anyone see who was in it?

18
00:01:32,842 --> 00:01:35,511
We'll just have to run the vehicle.

19
00:01:35,595 --> 00:01:38,681
Then we'll know who that woman is
and where Bulgae is in no time.

20
00:01:38,764 --> 00:01:40,308
- Right?
- Yeah.

21
00:01:41,183 --> 00:01:44,145
- Time to plan the next step!
- No. First things first.

22
00:01:45,062 --> 00:01:47,148
We need to wrap things up with Yoo In-gu.

23
00:01:47,231 --> 00:01:49,984
Come on, we got rid of the drugs
and secured the evidence.

24
00:01:50,067 --> 00:01:51,193
What else is there to do?

25
00:01:51,277 --> 00:01:54,155
We may have Yoo In-gu on a leash,
but it's not over.

26
00:01:54,238 --> 00:01:56,866
Yoo In-gu and Han Gyeong-wook
have connections with prosecutors.

27
00:01:56,949 --> 00:02:00,369
We could lose all the evidence
we worked so hard to get.

28
00:02:00,953 --> 00:02:02,788
If we want to indict Yoo In-gu
and Han Gyeong-wook

29
00:02:02,872 --> 00:02:03,956
we need Prosecutor Gang.

30
00:02:04,040 --> 00:02:06,584
So, Seong-won and Beom-ryong.

31
00:02:06,667 --> 00:02:09,920
Look for her in the CCTV feeds
that Gong-bok hacked into tomorrow.

32
00:02:10,004 --> 00:02:13,215
If she's still on Yeongseon Island,
she's bound to show up at some point.

33
00:02:13,299 --> 00:02:16,260
Gong-bok and I will look into Yoo In-gu.

34
00:02:16,344 --> 00:02:18,679
Me and Beom-ryong?

35
00:02:18,804 --> 00:02:20,931
Isn't Gong-bok better with CCTVs?

36
00:02:21,015 --> 00:02:24,268
Yeah, watching cams is his specialty.

37
00:02:24,810 --> 00:02:27,313
- Why me?
- Listen, man.

38
00:02:28,856 --> 00:02:30,107
Look.

39
00:02:31,484 --> 00:02:34,445
You overdid it tonight.
You should take it easy.

40
00:02:36,322 --> 00:02:37,948
What's gotten into him?

41
00:02:38,074 --> 00:02:40,534
I'm saying this for your own good.

42
00:02:40,618 --> 00:02:43,454
I just can't stand you
and your shaky legs, all right?

43
00:02:44,789 --> 00:02:47,708
Yeah, and my legs are fine.
I can handle it.

44
00:02:47,792 --> 00:02:49,085
Hey, my legs aren't shaky.

45
00:02:49,168 --> 00:02:51,962
Anyway, let's focus on wrapping up
the Yoo In-gu case for good.

46
00:02:52,046 --> 00:02:54,256
As for Bulgae, like you said,
we practically got him.

47
00:02:54,340 --> 00:02:56,384
- So there's no need to rush it.
- Okay.

48
00:02:56,467 --> 00:02:57,885
All right, drink up. Come on.

49
00:02:58,552 --> 00:03:00,763
- All right.
- Good work, everyone.

50
00:03:16,112 --> 00:03:17,822
You look troubled.

51
00:03:18,989 --> 00:03:20,241
Is it because of Bulgae?

52
00:03:22,243 --> 00:03:25,329
- You catch on quick, don't you?
- Hey.

53
00:03:25,996 --> 00:03:28,082
We finally found Bulgae after ten years.

54
00:03:28,165 --> 00:03:30,584
And you say, "Let's not rush things."

55
00:03:30,668 --> 00:03:32,420
That doesn't sound like you.

56
00:03:32,503 --> 00:03:34,505
You should be chomping at the bit
to catch him.

57
00:03:36,215 --> 00:03:38,801
What's going on? What's bothering you?

58
00:03:39,969 --> 00:03:40,970
Look.

59
00:03:41,971 --> 00:03:45,516
I saw the woman
who drove off with Bulgae earlier.

60
00:03:46,726 --> 00:03:48,728
It was the police officer
Gang Beom-ryong has a crush on.

61
00:03:50,271 --> 00:03:51,272
For real?

62
00:03:52,898 --> 00:03:53,899
That's just...

63
00:03:54,650 --> 00:03:56,819
What is she doing
with a North Korean agent?

64
00:03:56,902 --> 00:03:57,987
I don't know.

65
00:03:58,988 --> 00:04:00,948
I can't make sense of it.

66
00:04:01,907 --> 00:04:04,785
The fact that Bulgae is working
with a police officer.

67
00:04:04,869 --> 00:04:08,539
And that she happened to be the one
visiting Kim Seon-jung's house.

68
00:04:10,082 --> 00:04:12,460
We have to figure out
what those two are after.

69
00:04:12,543 --> 00:04:17,006
And more importantly,
whether they'll be getting in our way.

70
00:04:17,548 --> 00:04:20,760
Ma Gong-bok and I are going to
start looking into her tomorrow.

71
00:04:20,843 --> 00:04:21,844
Just so you know.

72
00:04:27,308 --> 00:04:30,019
Beom-ryong seemed to have
really fallen for that officer.

73
00:04:30,102 --> 00:04:31,937
That's why it's better he doesn't know.

74
00:04:32,646 --> 00:04:34,440
What good would come from him finding out

75
00:04:34,523 --> 00:04:36,525
the woman he has a crush on
is mixed up with Bulgae?

76
00:04:37,234 --> 00:04:39,653
I'll wrap this up as quickly as possible.

77
00:04:39,737 --> 00:04:43,240
You keep an eye on Gang Beom-ryong.

78
00:04:43,324 --> 00:04:44,366
You got it.

79
00:04:54,418 --> 00:04:56,253
WE OPPOSE YEONGSEON REDEVELOPMENT

80
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:02,384
Hey, you're up.

81
00:05:02,468 --> 00:05:04,303
- Nam-il.
- How are you feeling?

82
00:05:04,386 --> 00:05:06,806
Nam-il, are you okay?
Are you hurt anywhere?

83
00:05:07,181 --> 00:05:08,641
This is no time to worry about me.

84
00:05:09,266 --> 00:05:11,685
- You saved me yesterday.
- Yesterday?

85
00:05:12,436 --> 00:05:13,687
I did?

86
00:05:15,981 --> 00:05:17,066
You don't remember again?

87
00:05:17,942 --> 00:05:20,110
You turned into the Hulk yesterday.

88
00:05:20,194 --> 00:05:23,239
I heard you asked the prosecutor lady
to hit you on the head.

89
00:05:23,823 --> 00:05:26,492
That's right.
It looked like you were in danger.

90
00:05:26,575 --> 00:05:28,828
Geez, Uncle, are you crazy?
What if you had failed?

91
00:05:28,911 --> 00:05:31,831
If you hadn't been there,
none of this would've happened.

92
00:05:31,914 --> 00:05:34,583
Why were you at a drug deal
with gangsters? Huh?

93
00:05:35,292 --> 00:05:38,754
I got duped, okay?
They were paying a million won a day.

94
00:05:39,547 --> 00:05:41,048
Always trying to score big at once.

95
00:05:41,131 --> 00:05:43,050
- Were you--
- No, that wasn't it!

96
00:05:45,094 --> 00:05:46,303
I just wanted to make money.

97
00:05:47,012 --> 00:05:49,932
So I can get our house back
and get you out of here.

98
00:05:51,433 --> 00:05:53,978
I know you're going through hell
because of me.

99
00:05:56,647 --> 00:05:58,148
You haven't eaten, have you?

100
00:06:07,157 --> 00:06:09,869
Hello.
We're going to Heaven Capital, right?

101
00:06:09,952 --> 00:06:11,203
No.

102
00:06:11,287 --> 00:06:13,205
I thought we were
going to check on Yoo In-gu.

103
00:06:13,289 --> 00:06:15,833
Change of plans.
We're going to the police precinct.

104
00:06:15,916 --> 00:06:17,167
The police precinct?

105
00:06:17,793 --> 00:06:19,503
Okay.

106
00:06:19,587 --> 00:06:23,132
So these so-called Masked Racers
suddenly appeared out of nowhere

107
00:06:23,215 --> 00:06:24,758
and blew up all the drugs?

108
00:06:25,634 --> 00:06:27,678
And you let them get away?

109
00:06:28,804 --> 00:06:31,223
Yes, sir.
They certainly knew what they're doing.

110
00:06:36,353 --> 00:06:37,897
Yoo is so stupid!

111
00:06:38,898 --> 00:06:41,025
Can't do a damn thing right.

112
00:06:41,108 --> 00:06:42,401
Useless idiot.

113
00:06:50,784 --> 00:06:52,953
I can't get dragged into this mess
and get burned.

114
00:06:53,704 --> 00:06:55,289
I'd better fold.

115
00:06:57,333 --> 00:07:01,045
Mr. Geum, what's the status
on the Kangsik Sect rebuilding plan?

116
00:07:01,128 --> 00:07:03,589
I've already talked the boys into it.

117
00:07:03,672 --> 00:07:05,299
We just have to change the name.

118
00:07:05,549 --> 00:07:06,550
Okay.

119
00:07:06,634 --> 00:07:09,136
Good job.

120
00:07:12,264 --> 00:07:15,726
So, uh, Chairman, when should we start?

121
00:07:16,518 --> 00:07:17,811
Right now.

122
00:07:17,895 --> 00:07:20,689
Oh, you mean right now?

123
00:07:20,773 --> 00:07:21,815
Are you sure?

124
00:07:22,691 --> 00:07:25,402
Come on, how hard can it be
to take out one piece of trash?

125
00:07:25,486 --> 00:07:27,529
I'll take care of taking out the trash.

126
00:07:27,613 --> 00:07:30,658
You just look into the guys
who blew Yoo's drug deal.

127
00:07:30,741 --> 00:07:33,452
That martial arts master,
or Masked Racers, whoever they are.

128
00:07:33,535 --> 00:07:35,079
Those guys?

129
00:07:35,162 --> 00:07:37,206
They just popped out of nowhere
here in Yeongseon

130
00:07:37,289 --> 00:07:39,083
and keep thwarting our plans every time.

131
00:07:39,166 --> 00:07:40,626
We can't just let it slide.

132
00:07:40,709 --> 00:07:43,337
Who's to say they won't
get in the way of my business?

133
00:07:43,420 --> 00:07:45,631
It'd be best to eliminate them completely.

134
00:07:45,714 --> 00:07:47,925
So mobilize every cop you can.

135
00:07:48,008 --> 00:07:50,844
Scour all the CCTV and dash cam footage
around Yeongseon Port.

136
00:07:51,929 --> 00:07:54,890
Oh, and do it quietly,
so Yoo doesn't find out.

137
00:07:54,974 --> 00:07:57,059
Ah, don't you worry about that.

138
00:07:57,142 --> 00:08:00,062
He's in no state
to notice anything right now.

139
00:08:11,865 --> 00:08:15,160
I scraped together as much as I could.

140
00:08:16,161 --> 00:08:17,371
But this is all we've got.

141
00:08:25,921 --> 00:08:31,927
- Come on. I really need it today.
- Today's no good, okay?

142
00:08:32,011 --> 00:08:34,179
- Who are they?
- Uh, they're...

143
00:08:34,263 --> 00:08:37,182
Customers from the casino
who came to borrow money.

144
00:08:37,266 --> 00:08:39,935
But we're out of cash,
so we're sending them away.

145
00:08:40,519 --> 00:08:42,229
Out of cash?

146
00:08:55,284 --> 00:08:57,327
Hey, Boss!

147
00:08:57,411 --> 00:08:58,787
I can't breathe.

148
00:08:58,871 --> 00:09:01,874
You have to breathe, Boss!

149
00:09:06,587 --> 00:09:08,589
- Je-sun.
- Hey, Ms. Gang.

150
00:09:10,424 --> 00:09:12,384
- Are you okay?
- Oh, yes, I'm fine.

151
00:09:12,468 --> 00:09:14,803
- Oh, my.
- I'm not even hurt.

152
00:09:14,887 --> 00:09:16,972
I heard I ruined everything yesterday.

153
00:09:17,056 --> 00:09:18,140
I'm sorry.

154
00:09:18,223 --> 00:09:21,435
Oh, no. It wasn't just your fault.
Please don't worry about it.

155
00:09:23,062 --> 00:09:26,607
I heard you won't be able to
catch the Heaven Capital guys.

156
00:09:27,775 --> 00:09:30,069
So I've been thinking.

157
00:09:30,986 --> 00:09:33,572
Heaven Capital lost all of their drugs.

158
00:09:33,655 --> 00:09:36,033
So they're not just going to
sit back and watch.

159
00:09:36,116 --> 00:09:40,079
They're bound to do something
to make up for this mishap.

160
00:09:40,162 --> 00:09:42,664
So what if we use that to our advantage?

161
00:09:42,748 --> 00:09:43,832
How?

162
00:09:43,916 --> 00:09:46,835
We have no way of knowing
what they're up to.

163
00:09:47,753 --> 00:09:49,213
There is someone who would know.

164
00:09:54,468 --> 00:09:58,555
So you want me to be a double agent?

165
00:09:58,639 --> 00:09:59,890
A double agent?

166
00:10:01,850 --> 00:10:04,311
- Do you think I'm crazy?
- You have two options.

167
00:10:04,978 --> 00:10:08,816
First, you could come with me
and turn yourself in.

168
00:10:08,899 --> 00:10:11,860
Aiding and abetting a murder.
Destruction of evidence.

169
00:10:11,944 --> 00:10:15,489
Accepting bribes.
I'm going to throw the book at you.

170
00:10:15,572 --> 00:10:17,366
In that case, dear Sergeant Kim...

171
00:10:17,449 --> 00:10:22,913
Not only will you lose your badge,
but also rot behind bars for 30 years.

172
00:10:23,497 --> 00:10:27,209
Come on, Prosecutor.
This is unfair. I'm the victim here.

173
00:10:27,292 --> 00:10:29,711
I'm telling you,
I've been completely wronged.

174
00:10:29,795 --> 00:10:31,046
Then, option two.

175
00:10:32,089 --> 00:10:33,715
Go back to your precinct.

176
00:10:33,799 --> 00:10:36,510
Find out what Heaven Capital is up to.

177
00:10:36,593 --> 00:10:38,720
And report everything to us in real time.

178
00:10:38,804 --> 00:10:42,391
Do that, and I'll do everything I can
to get you a lighter sentence.

179
00:10:44,268 --> 00:10:45,269
So?

180
00:10:46,186 --> 00:10:47,521
What will it be?

181
00:10:56,947 --> 00:10:58,448
So, like...

182
00:10:59,408 --> 00:11:03,120
- I just have to give you the intel?
- Yes.

183
00:11:04,079 --> 00:11:06,832
But are you sure it's okay to let him go?

184
00:11:06,915 --> 00:11:09,835
This guy blackmails people
the first chance he gets.

185
00:11:09,918 --> 00:11:13,338
He's right.
A traitor is always going to be a traitor.

186
00:11:13,422 --> 00:11:14,631
No.

187
00:11:15,716 --> 00:11:17,467
I'll watch him closely.

188
00:11:18,552 --> 00:11:20,179
- You will?
- Yes.

189
00:11:28,770 --> 00:11:30,147
Hey, Mr. Jo.

190
00:11:30,731 --> 00:11:33,400
Is Prosecutor Gang
really on Yeongseon Island?

191
00:11:33,483 --> 00:11:35,527
There's not a single trace of her.

192
00:11:37,154 --> 00:11:40,407
What, did you expect her
to magically appear like in a movie?

193
00:11:41,408 --> 00:11:43,994
This whole tracking business?

194
00:11:44,077 --> 00:11:46,079
It's a game of patience. A waiting game.

195
00:11:46,163 --> 00:11:47,873
Yeah, but still.

196
00:11:47,956 --> 00:11:50,167
It's like finding a needle in a haystack.

197
00:11:50,250 --> 00:11:52,461
Patience, patience.

198
00:11:53,462 --> 00:11:54,588
Patience.

199
00:11:55,672 --> 00:11:57,549
RESTRICTED NUMBER

200
00:12:03,013 --> 00:12:05,307
Hey, I need to take this call.

201
00:12:05,390 --> 00:12:06,642
Okay.

202
00:12:10,896 --> 00:12:12,272
Yes, Boss. What is it?

203
00:12:12,356 --> 00:12:15,943
Listen, I need you to come visit me today.

204
00:12:16,985 --> 00:12:18,528
Now? What for?

205
00:12:18,654 --> 00:12:21,114
Do I only call you when something's up?

206
00:12:21,782 --> 00:12:25,994
I'm curious about how things are going
with Prosecutor Gang.

207
00:12:26,995 --> 00:12:28,622
What, are you busy?

208
00:12:29,289 --> 00:12:30,999
No, sir. I'll be right there.

209
00:12:31,083 --> 00:12:33,168
All right. Don't be late.

210
00:12:43,220 --> 00:12:44,471
Oh, man.

211
00:12:53,397 --> 00:12:55,274
I'm sorry about this.

212
00:12:55,357 --> 00:12:58,360
But you'll have to handle
the CCTV duty alone.

213
00:13:00,070 --> 00:13:01,405
Why all of a sudden?

214
00:13:03,156 --> 00:13:04,616
Well...

215
00:13:04,700 --> 00:13:06,785
I have to get things sorted at the store.

216
00:13:07,786 --> 00:13:10,205
Corporate called me in.

217
00:13:11,498 --> 00:13:12,582
I'll be back soon.

218
00:13:14,293 --> 00:13:16,378
Make it quick.
My eyes get sore looking at the screen.

219
00:13:16,461 --> 00:13:17,462
Okay.

220
00:13:43,739 --> 00:13:44,906
Director.

221
00:13:44,990 --> 00:13:46,616
I think you need to take a look.

222
00:13:51,288 --> 00:13:52,539
- Here.
- What is it?

223
00:13:52,622 --> 00:13:55,125
We weren't expecting a deposit this large.

224
00:13:55,208 --> 00:13:56,501
Do you know anything about it?

225
00:13:57,878 --> 00:13:58,920
No.

226
00:14:02,174 --> 00:14:03,508
Where's Mr. Park?

227
00:14:04,426 --> 00:14:06,094
I was just about to tell you.

228
00:14:06,178 --> 00:14:08,680
Mr. Park didn't show up today
without any notice.

229
00:14:15,103 --> 00:14:16,188
MR. PARK SEONG-HWAN

230
00:14:20,484 --> 00:14:22,986
The number you have dialed...

231
00:14:26,573 --> 00:14:28,408
Can I get a bowl of soup here?

232
00:14:33,163 --> 00:14:34,206
Thank you.

233
00:14:36,166 --> 00:14:39,252
What brings you out here, Mr. Han?

234
00:14:41,171 --> 00:14:42,964
I thought we were done talking.

235
00:14:44,049 --> 00:14:45,050
Take a look.

236
00:14:53,433 --> 00:14:54,976
DETAILS ON ILLEGAL POLITICAL FUNDS
RAISED THROUGH ORPHANAGE

237
00:14:58,980 --> 00:15:00,232
ARTWORK SOLD FOR ILLEGAL POLITICAL FUNDS

238
00:15:06,154 --> 00:15:08,240
RECEIVING AND SELLING OFF OF ARTWORK

239
00:15:11,576 --> 00:15:12,661
YEONGSEON ORPHANAGE TRANSACTIONS

240
00:15:20,127 --> 00:15:24,005
Are you trying to blackmail me
with these fabricated documents?

241
00:15:24,089 --> 00:15:25,340
Fabricated?

242
00:15:26,425 --> 00:15:29,344
Didn't your wife receive them
just the other day?

243
00:15:29,761 --> 00:15:33,306
Various books and expensive pieces of art.

244
00:15:35,016 --> 00:15:38,770
- Don't tell me all of that was--
- I never would have imagined it.

245
00:15:38,854 --> 00:15:42,691
The great Mr. Kim Seon-jung,
ever the righteous educator.

246
00:15:43,275 --> 00:15:47,696
To think he'd even use his spouse
to raise political funds.

247
00:15:48,947 --> 00:15:50,282
You...

248
00:15:51,324 --> 00:15:53,743
It's not too late for you to pull out.

249
00:15:53,827 --> 00:15:56,705
Once you do, this information
won't make it into the news.

250
00:15:56,788 --> 00:16:01,460
And your reputation as a noble educator

251
00:16:01,543 --> 00:16:02,878
will remain untarnished.

252
00:16:06,882 --> 00:16:10,844
I'm not afraid of my reputation
being run through the mud.

253
00:16:11,636 --> 00:16:13,221
I wouldn't have run for office if I were.

254
00:16:14,890 --> 00:16:18,059
In fact, seeing this
only strengthens my resolve.

255
00:16:19,144 --> 00:16:21,229
I don't care
if I'll have to run through the mud.

256
00:16:22,147 --> 00:16:25,609
I have to stop a swindler like you

257
00:16:26,610 --> 00:16:28,028
from becoming mayor.

258
00:16:34,618 --> 00:16:40,540
It's so obvious that you've only swum
in the cleanest of waters.

259
00:16:40,624 --> 00:16:44,753
You have no idea what lies
in the abyss at the bottom of the river.

260
00:16:45,962 --> 00:16:50,258
Do you know what I learned from dealing
with all sorts of people at the NIS?

261
00:16:51,927 --> 00:16:57,432
In the face of true agony,
innocence is utterly useless.

262
00:16:59,434 --> 00:17:01,978
How painful do you think it will be

263
00:17:02,062 --> 00:17:04,564
when this news goes public?

264
00:17:04,648 --> 00:17:07,651
Will it be a little slap on the wrist?

265
00:17:07,734 --> 00:17:09,945
The public will turn against you.

266
00:17:10,028 --> 00:17:13,406
It won't matter how much
you claim to be innocent.

267
00:17:13,490 --> 00:17:15,033
Nobody will want to listen.

268
00:17:15,825 --> 00:17:17,494
Your beloved orphanage.

269
00:17:17,577 --> 00:17:20,789
It will be branded as a front
for illegal activity and destroyed.

270
00:17:21,414 --> 00:17:23,500
And what about your followers?

271
00:17:24,125 --> 00:17:26,044
They'll be afraid to be seen
as one of your people.

272
00:17:26,670 --> 00:17:28,213
They won't dare say a word.

273
00:17:28,964 --> 00:17:30,966
And guess how it'll all end?

274
00:17:31,049 --> 00:17:34,761
You will crawl through
years of endless, tedious trials.

275
00:17:34,844 --> 00:17:38,848
And you and your wife will be in and out
of detention centers and prisons.

276
00:17:39,641 --> 00:17:41,184
Answer me this.

277
00:17:41,268 --> 00:17:46,648
Would you still be able to
stay on your high horse after all that?

278
00:17:47,315 --> 00:17:51,736
Would you look down at me and lecture me
about justice and innocence?

279
00:17:54,739 --> 00:17:56,616
You see, the thing is

280
00:17:57,617 --> 00:17:59,619
I've never seen anyone like that.

281
00:18:39,659 --> 00:18:42,746
But this guy, Sergeant Kim,
isn't he in cahoots with Yoo In-gu?

282
00:18:42,829 --> 00:18:45,999
He is. A corrupt cop
that Yoo In-gu paid off.

283
00:18:46,082 --> 00:18:49,794
So you think Bulgae teamed up
with both Yoo In-gu and Kim Seon-jung?

284
00:18:50,587 --> 00:18:52,756
He was running from Yoo In-gu
just yesterday.

285
00:18:52,839 --> 00:18:55,216
You think they've teamed up?
That makes no sense.

286
00:18:55,300 --> 00:18:56,718
No.

287
00:18:56,801 --> 00:18:59,554
With that cop, it makes perfect sense.

288
00:18:59,638 --> 00:19:03,308
Honestly, she seemed
very suspicious to me.

289
00:19:03,391 --> 00:19:04,559
Why is that?

290
00:19:04,643 --> 00:19:08,563
For three years, after her patrol,
she'd come to our convenience store.

291
00:19:08,647 --> 00:19:09,981
And she only gets those lunch boxes.

292
00:19:10,065 --> 00:19:12,400
Here's the thing about those lunch boxes.

293
00:19:12,484 --> 00:19:14,444
You can't eat them every day
without getting sick of them.

294
00:19:14,527 --> 00:19:17,489
I always thought that was weird,
and recently

295
00:19:18,198 --> 00:19:20,492
she started giving the boss these looks.

296
00:19:20,575 --> 00:19:23,244
I mean, honestly,
a gorgeous woman like that?

297
00:19:23,328 --> 00:19:26,081
Do you think
she'd actually be interested in him?

298
00:19:26,164 --> 00:19:27,666
Let's be real, that makes no sense.

299
00:19:27,749 --> 00:19:29,250
I've known him for ten years.

300
00:19:29,334 --> 00:19:31,211
And his face still scares me sometimes.

301
00:19:32,462 --> 00:19:34,923
So she approached
Gang Beom-ryong on purpose?

302
00:19:35,006 --> 00:19:37,509
She must have figured out
he was Hwasan Sect's number two.

303
00:19:37,592 --> 00:19:39,594
She was planning on
using him from the start.

304
00:19:42,389 --> 00:19:43,598
Hold on.

305
00:19:44,641 --> 00:19:46,184
You seem a little too excited.

306
00:19:46,267 --> 00:19:48,019
Are you happy
that your boss is being used?

307
00:19:50,897 --> 00:19:52,565
No, not really.

308
00:19:53,316 --> 00:19:55,568
I'm just worried, that's all.

309
00:19:55,652 --> 00:19:58,029
He could totally fall for
a shady woman like her

310
00:19:58,113 --> 00:20:00,323
and ruin his entire life.

311
00:20:00,865 --> 00:20:03,159
Nothing's for sure yet,
so let's just wait and see.

312
00:20:03,743 --> 00:20:07,163
And until we're certain,
don't let Gang Beom-ryong find out.

313
00:20:09,124 --> 00:20:10,250
Yeah, sure.

314
00:20:19,801 --> 00:20:22,095
Yesterday? It looked just like last time.

315
00:20:22,220 --> 00:20:25,265
You suddenly went nuts
and started doing these weird steps.

316
00:20:25,348 --> 00:20:26,599
You kicked everyone around you.

317
00:21:08,057 --> 00:21:09,184
What are you doing?

318
00:21:15,774 --> 00:21:18,651
I was just trying to see
if something would jog my memory.

319
00:21:24,115 --> 00:21:25,742
Want me to help you with that?

320
00:21:25,825 --> 00:21:27,494
- Huh?
- I mean...

321
00:21:28,203 --> 00:21:29,746
You probably didn't know this.

322
00:21:30,747 --> 00:21:32,624
But I was in Violent Crimes
before I was a prosecutor.

323
00:21:33,416 --> 00:21:37,337
I've handled so many cases
that I can just look at someone's face

324
00:21:37,420 --> 00:21:40,048
and observe their behavior and belongings

325
00:21:40,131 --> 00:21:42,133
to get a pretty good idea
of the life they've led.

326
00:21:42,217 --> 00:21:44,219
Wow, you can really do that?

327
00:21:45,887 --> 00:21:48,848
Did you have any belongings with you
ten years back

328
00:21:48,932 --> 00:21:51,059
when you were found on that beach?

329
00:21:51,142 --> 00:21:54,312
If I see them, I might be able
to figure out what you used to do.

330
00:21:54,395 --> 00:21:56,773
I could at least make an educated guess.

331
00:21:59,943 --> 00:22:01,528
Belongings?

332
00:22:08,243 --> 00:22:09,244
PARK MI-KYUNG

333
00:22:13,665 --> 00:22:16,501
YEONGSEON POLICE SUBSTATION

334
00:22:16,584 --> 00:22:18,294
What now?

335
00:22:22,215 --> 00:22:24,384
You still have to carry out your duties.

336
00:22:25,385 --> 00:22:27,011
Do I really have to?

337
00:22:27,095 --> 00:22:29,305
We're both cops.
Can't you just let it slide?

338
00:22:29,389 --> 00:22:32,308
We may both be cops,
but we're at different levels.

339
00:22:37,814 --> 00:22:41,067
Oh, hey, Sergeant Kim.
I was just about to call you.

340
00:22:41,150 --> 00:22:44,070
Hey, sorry for calling so late, Boss.

341
00:22:44,153 --> 00:22:45,905
So, what happened with yesterday's deal?

342
00:22:45,989 --> 00:22:48,116
I only heard that things got
blown up and stuff.

343
00:22:48,199 --> 00:22:51,119
It was a total shitshow.
This whole place is, too.

344
00:22:51,202 --> 00:22:53,872
Oh my goodness.
That is just terrible news.

345
00:22:56,457 --> 00:22:59,669
Anyway, I have something to tell you
regarding that.

346
00:22:59,752 --> 00:23:03,214
- Are you free right now?
- You want me there right now?

347
00:23:05,675 --> 00:23:08,052
Yes, of course. I'll be right there.

348
00:23:08,136 --> 00:23:11,681
By the way, Boss.
I've got a new recruit with me.

349
00:23:11,764 --> 00:23:13,474
Is there room for one more?

350
00:23:14,434 --> 00:23:15,852
Yes, Boss.

351
00:23:25,445 --> 00:23:26,821
There they are. They're coming out.

352
00:23:27,238 --> 00:23:30,450
Those dirty cops are on the move.
Something's definitely up. Hurry.

353
00:23:31,451 --> 00:23:32,452
Start the car, quick.

354
00:23:32,535 --> 00:23:35,538
God, stop being so loud.
I'm starting it now.

355
00:23:35,622 --> 00:23:36,998
Come on. We're going to lose them!

356
00:23:37,081 --> 00:23:39,250
- Just buckle up.
- Seriously?

357
00:23:43,463 --> 00:23:44,631
They're taking off!

358
00:23:47,175 --> 00:23:49,469
- Come on, get on their tail!
- Will you shut up?

359
00:24:07,528 --> 00:24:11,032
- I'm sorry I'm late.
- Hey, why are you always so late?

360
00:24:23,795 --> 00:24:24,796
Oh?

361
00:24:26,714 --> 00:24:27,757
And who is this?

362
00:24:28,758 --> 00:24:30,718
Introduce yourself. Go on. Say hi.

363
00:24:31,678 --> 00:24:34,055
It's a pleasure to meet you.
I'm Officer Park Mi-kyung.

364
00:24:35,431 --> 00:24:37,767
So you're the recruit he mentioned.

365
00:24:37,850 --> 00:24:39,185
Oh, yes.

366
00:24:39,268 --> 00:24:41,604
She's sharp,
so I thought she could be of help.

367
00:24:41,688 --> 00:24:42,689
Oh, is that so?

368
00:24:44,857 --> 00:24:47,986
- Hello. I'm Geum Kang-sik.
- Hi.

369
00:24:49,696 --> 00:24:51,155
Ever the gentleman.

370
00:24:55,576 --> 00:24:57,620
But why did you want to meet at the port?

371
00:24:57,704 --> 00:24:58,955
I heard the deal fell through.

372
00:24:59,038 --> 00:25:00,790
Yeah, obviously, it did.

373
00:25:00,873 --> 00:25:04,752
That's exactly what I need you two for.

374
00:25:05,253 --> 00:25:09,841
You see all these dashcams
and surveillance cams around?

375
00:25:09,924 --> 00:25:11,509
Bring me all the footage from them.

376
00:25:11,926 --> 00:25:13,386
Huh? Why?

377
00:25:13,469 --> 00:25:15,430
Stop asking so many questions!

378
00:25:15,513 --> 00:25:20,268
I got a special order to find out
who sabotaged the deal last night.

379
00:25:20,727 --> 00:25:23,938
With enough digging,
hopefully, I can pick up their trail.

380
00:25:26,232 --> 00:25:28,568
So, Ms. Park,
you sure you can handle this?

381
00:25:28,651 --> 00:25:32,155
I'm just a little worried
since you're a new face.

382
00:25:32,238 --> 00:25:34,824
Patrolling is my specialty. Don't worry.

383
00:25:37,285 --> 00:25:38,786
Her specialty is patrolling!

384
00:25:38,870 --> 00:25:40,413
Specialty, huh? Well, that's just perfect.

385
00:25:40,496 --> 00:25:43,249
Put those skills to use
and find something good for me.

386
00:25:43,332 --> 00:25:46,085
And I'll make sure
you get a nice incentive for it.

387
00:25:46,169 --> 00:25:50,173
Wow, an incentive!
President Yoo is always so generous!

388
00:25:50,256 --> 00:25:51,799
Keep it down, you ass.

389
00:25:51,883 --> 00:25:53,718
He can't ever find out
about this, all right?

390
00:25:53,801 --> 00:25:54,802
What?

391
00:25:55,178 --> 00:25:56,929
Isn't this an order from President Yoo?

392
00:25:58,347 --> 00:26:02,351
Listen up, okay? Yoo is done for.

393
00:26:02,435 --> 00:26:05,897
If you don't want to end up the same,
I'd start by deleting his number.

394
00:26:05,980 --> 00:26:08,149
And if he calls, don't answer. Got it?

395
00:26:08,232 --> 00:26:09,233
Yes.

396
00:26:09,317 --> 00:26:12,779
But who gave this special order?

397
00:26:14,280 --> 00:26:18,326
Chairman Do of Heaven Casino.
You wouldn't know.

398
00:26:25,249 --> 00:26:27,919
I think those bastards are looking for us.

399
00:26:28,336 --> 00:26:30,004
Do you think they might be onto us?

400
00:26:30,088 --> 00:26:32,840
We followed the exact route I planned.

401
00:26:32,924 --> 00:26:35,343
- No chance.
- You never know.

402
00:26:37,470 --> 00:26:40,640
We shouldn't just be
watching that officer.

403
00:26:40,723 --> 00:26:43,142
Shouldn't we have stepped up
and done something about it?

404
00:26:43,226 --> 00:26:45,436
Hey, I told you.

405
00:26:45,520 --> 00:26:47,688
Our target isn't the officer. It's Bulgae.

406
00:26:49,232 --> 00:26:50,817
Just watch quietly, will you?

407
00:26:51,692 --> 00:26:53,236
You have no patience.

408
00:26:58,157 --> 00:26:59,534
No patience?

409
00:27:01,202 --> 00:27:02,745
Mr. Jeong.

410
00:27:02,829 --> 00:27:04,413
I think you got the wrong idea.

411
00:27:04,497 --> 00:27:08,626
Beom-ryong and I have spent ten years
planning to avenge our big boss.

412
00:27:08,709 --> 00:27:10,920
Always holding back,
being patient, and enduring.

413
00:27:13,005 --> 00:27:14,465
How admirable.

414
00:27:14,549 --> 00:27:15,925
What's so great about that boss of yours?

415
00:27:18,219 --> 00:27:20,638
Mr. Jeong,
you can say that in front of me.

416
00:27:20,721 --> 00:27:23,683
But don't ever say that
in front of Beom-ryong.

417
00:27:23,766 --> 00:27:25,643
To him, the big boss?

418
00:27:25,726 --> 00:27:28,855
He was a mentor
and a father who took him in.

419
00:27:29,981 --> 00:27:33,901
If anyone insults or disobeys the big boss
in front of Beom-ryong

420
00:27:33,985 --> 00:27:36,320
that means they're at war with Beom-ryong.
You got that?

421
00:27:37,238 --> 00:27:38,990
So stupid.

422
00:27:39,073 --> 00:27:41,868
All of that respect
and loyalty you waste on him.

423
00:27:41,951 --> 00:27:44,328
Do you think your boss in prison
gives a damn about you?

424
00:27:44,871 --> 00:27:48,749
People never see
a loyal subordinate as a person.

425
00:27:49,625 --> 00:27:51,169
They see them as an obedient dog.

426
00:27:51,919 --> 00:27:54,338
Is that from personal experience?
Why are you so cynical?

427
00:27:55,047 --> 00:27:56,841
You must have been
screwed over by someone.

428
00:27:57,884 --> 00:28:02,013
Just a word of advice
from an NIS Agent who's seen it all.

429
00:28:02,096 --> 00:28:03,097
Be careful.

430
00:28:15,651 --> 00:28:18,112
Boss, is there something wrong?

431
00:28:18,196 --> 00:28:19,697
Nothing's wrong.

432
00:28:19,780 --> 00:28:23,367
I told you I just wanted to see you.

433
00:28:23,451 --> 00:28:26,287
So, how are things going
with Prosecutor Gang?

434
00:28:28,331 --> 00:28:29,332
It's all good.

435
00:28:30,124 --> 00:28:32,126
- Having any trouble?
- Not yet.

436
00:28:32,960 --> 00:28:35,254
I don't have enough to report back with.

437
00:28:36,047 --> 00:28:37,506
I'll let you know
once everything is settled.

438
00:28:39,258 --> 00:28:42,762
I must be bothering you
when you're busy, huh?

439
00:28:42,845 --> 00:28:43,846
Not at all, Boss.

440
00:28:43,930 --> 00:28:46,724
Maybe it's because
I've been in here for a while.

441
00:28:46,807 --> 00:28:48,851
I might be getting a little sentimental.

442
00:28:48,935 --> 00:28:50,978
I've been thinking a lot
about the old days.

443
00:28:51,979 --> 00:28:55,858
How many guys stabbed me in the back
over the last 30 years?

444
00:28:55,942 --> 00:28:58,319
- Do you remember?
- Twelve.

445
00:28:58,402 --> 00:28:59,528
Twelve.

446
00:29:01,030 --> 00:29:03,950
Among them was
my childhood friend of 40 years.

447
00:29:04,033 --> 00:29:07,787
And a kid who was like a son to me.

448
00:29:09,705 --> 00:29:14,752
Being betrayed by all of them
and having ended up like this...

449
00:29:14,835 --> 00:29:19,715
I'm starting to think
maybe I lived my life all wrong.

450
00:29:21,759 --> 00:29:23,970
- My mind's all over the place.
- That's not true, Boss.

451
00:29:24,053 --> 00:29:25,429
That's absolutely not true, Boss.

452
00:29:27,223 --> 00:29:29,016
But I've really thought about it.

453
00:29:29,850 --> 00:29:33,062
Even though twelve guys betrayed me,
there was this one kid.

454
00:29:33,145 --> 00:29:34,188
Gang Beom-ryong.

455
00:29:35,356 --> 00:29:38,526
He stayed by my side
with the strength of 100 men.

456
00:29:39,110 --> 00:29:41,946
You have no idea how reassuring that was.

457
00:29:43,281 --> 00:29:46,033
So what can I do, huh?

458
00:29:46,867 --> 00:29:49,412
Hwang Hwa-san was a man
who had lost all faith in people.

459
00:29:49,495 --> 00:29:51,789
A man who couldn't even trust
his own wife and kids.

460
00:29:51,872 --> 00:29:55,126
But he knew he could count on
Gang Beom-ryong no matter what.

461
00:29:58,629 --> 00:29:59,630
I'll make it worthwhile.

462
00:30:01,299 --> 00:30:02,466
Beom-ryong.

463
00:30:03,134 --> 00:30:05,761
You'll always be the only one

464
00:30:07,513 --> 00:30:08,681
I can count on.

465
00:30:09,515 --> 00:30:10,766
You know that, right?

466
00:30:12,810 --> 00:30:14,312
Yes, I understand.

467
00:30:26,073 --> 00:30:30,745
You'll always be the only one
I can count on.

468
00:30:34,248 --> 00:30:35,249
I'm sorry.

469
00:30:39,045 --> 00:30:44,300
I take it your chat didn't go so well.

470
00:31:17,666 --> 00:31:18,834
Okay, I see.

471
00:31:20,336 --> 00:31:24,965
So this is what you were wearing
when you fell in the ocean?

472
00:31:26,592 --> 00:31:28,969
- Yes.
- But...

473
00:31:29,637 --> 00:31:30,805
This...

474
00:31:31,806 --> 00:31:33,766
Why would you have been wearing this?

475
00:31:34,934 --> 00:31:36,143
Well...

476
00:31:36,602 --> 00:31:40,439
It's absolutely not a reflection
of my personal taste.

477
00:31:40,523 --> 00:31:43,651
I'm really not interested
in women's clothes.

478
00:31:43,734 --> 00:31:45,861
I just can't remember
no matter how hard I think about it.

479
00:31:45,945 --> 00:31:49,073
- Why I fell in the ocean with these.
- Okay, now.

480
00:31:50,908 --> 00:31:52,159
Moving on.

481
00:31:53,327 --> 00:31:55,079
Were there any other belongings?

482
00:31:55,162 --> 00:31:59,500
The man who found me said
all I had was an ID and a photo.

483
00:31:59,583 --> 00:32:01,085
So they ran my background.

484
00:32:01,168 --> 00:32:03,796
But I had no family
or anyone who was looking for me.

485
00:32:03,879 --> 00:32:06,632
- What about the photo?
- Right, the photo.

486
00:32:10,428 --> 00:32:12,513
I can't tell what it's a picture of.

487
00:32:13,639 --> 00:32:16,392
It looks like a postcard
or a photo from a magazine.

488
00:32:16,475 --> 00:32:18,436
What do you think?

489
00:32:19,770 --> 00:32:21,313
I'm just asking.

490
00:32:21,397 --> 00:32:27,361
What would you do if your past self
was a completely different person?

491
00:32:28,571 --> 00:32:31,240
- Huh?
- I mean, it's a possibility.

492
00:32:31,323 --> 00:32:34,493
What if you found out you were
a serial killer or whatever?

493
00:32:34,577 --> 00:32:36,787
Would you still want to
find out about your past?

494
00:32:42,793 --> 00:32:46,630
I've considered that my past might be
something difficult to accept.

495
00:32:46,714 --> 00:32:50,426
But I still want to find out.

496
00:32:51,760 --> 00:32:54,346
My past is a part of me, after all.

497
00:32:56,682 --> 00:32:57,975
I'm already prepared.

498
00:32:59,768 --> 00:33:02,354
No matter what kind of person
I was in the past...

499
00:33:03,981 --> 00:33:05,357
I'm going to try.

500
00:33:07,067 --> 00:33:09,111
And I'm going to accept it.

501
00:33:32,384 --> 00:33:34,970
Well then, I'll be on my way.

502
00:33:48,192 --> 00:33:51,445
- No need to sit. This'll be quick.
- What?

503
00:33:58,327 --> 00:33:59,703
Please kill me, sir!

504
00:34:00,120 --> 00:34:02,456
- I'll explain everything.
- What difference will that make?

505
00:34:02,540 --> 00:34:06,126
- Failure is failure.
- Deputy Director Han.

506
00:34:06,210 --> 00:34:10,506
Frankly, I don't care if you sell drugs
or kill a prosecutor.

507
00:34:10,589 --> 00:34:15,511
If the job ends successfully
without any loose ends, that is.

508
00:34:16,262 --> 00:34:20,641
I could've even turned a blind eye
to you going rogue.

509
00:34:20,724 --> 00:34:22,059
But here's the thing.

510
00:34:25,354 --> 00:34:28,399
How could you mess it up this badly?

511
00:34:28,482 --> 00:34:29,900
I'll take care of it all.

512
00:34:29,984 --> 00:34:32,403
I'll hunt down the masked bastards
who screwed up the deal.

513
00:34:32,486 --> 00:34:34,071
I'll somehow cover the funds--

514
00:34:34,154 --> 00:34:35,781
It's not about you taking care of it.

515
00:34:37,032 --> 00:34:38,951
You need to take responsibility.

516
00:34:42,830 --> 00:34:46,250
Pull out of all your businesses
and hand them over to Chairman Do.

517
00:34:47,876 --> 00:34:50,045
Deputy Director Han,
how can I just hand my businesses over?

518
00:34:50,129 --> 00:34:51,630
I think there's been a misunderstanding.

519
00:34:51,714 --> 00:34:54,425
- He's done with you. Get out.
- This is so unfair.

520
00:35:00,806 --> 00:35:01,849
Unfair?

521
00:35:02,725 --> 00:35:04,727
A lot of people tell me that.

522
00:35:04,810 --> 00:35:06,979
"It's unfair. I did nothing wrong."

523
00:35:07,855 --> 00:35:10,065
You know what those guys have in common?

524
00:35:10,149 --> 00:35:13,402
Just two hours alone with them,
and their faces change like that.

525
00:35:14,486 --> 00:35:18,365
And then they suddenly
start begging for their lives.

526
00:35:19,199 --> 00:35:21,744
And they list everything they did wrong.

527
00:35:26,081 --> 00:35:27,333
How do you think you'll hold up?

528
00:35:37,176 --> 00:35:38,260
Secretary Baek.

529
00:35:39,136 --> 00:35:40,512
Let me ask you one thing.

530
00:35:41,180 --> 00:35:43,682
Did that bastard Do Hyeon-tae
set this whole thing up?

531
00:36:01,784 --> 00:36:03,702
- Kang-sik.
- Yes.

532
00:36:03,786 --> 00:36:06,664
- Gather all of our boys.
- What are you planning, Boss?

533
00:36:07,831 --> 00:36:10,459
The lid on my coffin hasn't shut yet.
I should at least put up a fight.

534
00:36:10,542 --> 00:36:12,127
We're getting Chairman Do tonight.

535
00:36:12,211 --> 00:36:14,338
Boss, that's too dangerous.

536
00:36:14,421 --> 00:36:18,092
Don't give me that shit.
I just lost everything to that bastard.

537
00:36:18,175 --> 00:36:20,886
I can't let him get away with this.
I couldn't live with myself.

538
00:36:21,470 --> 00:36:24,348
I'm going to take him down
and get my businesses back.

539
00:36:24,473 --> 00:36:26,642
And then I'll settle the score
with Han Gyeong-wook.

540
00:36:27,559 --> 00:36:28,811
You got that?

541
00:36:29,603 --> 00:36:32,189
Understood, Boss. I'll get them ready.

542
00:36:32,272 --> 00:36:35,734
Good. I'll show them
what kind of man I am.

543
00:36:45,119 --> 00:36:46,203
You must be tired.

544
00:36:47,955 --> 00:36:50,791
That son of a bitch Yoo In-gu
had to go and do something stupid.

545
00:36:50,874 --> 00:36:52,710
This is going to be a headache.

546
00:36:52,793 --> 00:36:55,087
But won't Chairman Do
manage the businesses well enough?

547
00:36:55,170 --> 00:36:58,549
Chairman Do is useless
besides running a business.

548
00:37:00,092 --> 00:37:04,388
At least Yoo In-gu was useful
for doing the dirty work.

549
00:37:04,471 --> 00:37:08,225
Didn't Chairman Do say he'd find
a capable replacement for Yoo In-gu?

550
00:37:08,308 --> 00:37:12,062
We have to make sure
the Yeongseon project goes smoothly.

551
00:37:13,063 --> 00:37:14,565
Guys like them won't cut it.

552
00:37:17,985 --> 00:37:20,612
We need someone
who's been through the chaos.

553
00:37:20,696 --> 00:37:23,407
A seasoned veteran
needs to be put in charge.

554
00:37:31,290 --> 00:37:33,250
SENDING FILES RELATED TO
THE FERRY SHIP INCIDENT

555
00:37:33,333 --> 00:37:35,252
2016 FERRY CCTV

556
00:37:50,684 --> 00:37:52,561
It wasn't an unidentified woman.

557
00:37:52,895 --> 00:37:54,646
It was Je-sun.

558
00:38:01,195 --> 00:38:02,237
North Korea.

559
00:38:03,322 --> 00:38:05,282
TWO NIS AGENTS CAUGHT BEFORE
COLLUDING WITH NORTH KOREA, GONE MISSING

560
00:38:05,365 --> 00:38:06,700
National Intelligence Service.

561
00:38:12,748 --> 00:38:17,127
Today is the day that decides
the fate of the Ingu Sect.

562
00:38:17,211 --> 00:38:21,048
Will we let a fox like Do take what's ours
and live as nobodies in this world?

563
00:38:21,131 --> 00:38:23,675
Or will you follow me and rise up?

564
00:38:24,676 --> 00:38:26,178
It's all up to you.

565
00:38:27,304 --> 00:38:29,306
- Got it?
- Yes, Boss!

566
00:38:31,391 --> 00:38:32,434
Boss!

567
00:38:34,895 --> 00:38:37,648
Chairman Do is in the penthouse right now.

568
00:38:37,731 --> 00:38:38,816
What about his security?

569
00:38:38,899 --> 00:38:41,068
I confirmed everyone went home,
even Director Nam.

570
00:38:42,277 --> 00:38:43,570
Let's go.

571
00:39:32,077 --> 00:39:34,162
Wow. Nice timing, President Yoo.

572
00:39:34,246 --> 00:39:35,289
You're right on time.

573
00:39:35,372 --> 00:39:37,040
What the hell do you think you're doing?

574
00:39:37,124 --> 00:39:38,208
Can't you read the room?

575
00:39:38,292 --> 00:39:42,170
Oh, please.
I know exactly what's going on.

576
00:39:43,547 --> 00:39:44,965
You're here to get rid of me, right?

577
00:39:45,841 --> 00:39:48,010
And you're still sitting here
popping champagne?

578
00:39:51,221 --> 00:39:52,222
Here.

579
00:40:06,695 --> 00:40:10,699
This is a historic moment
where Ingu Sect becomes Kangsik Sect.

580
00:40:11,658 --> 00:40:13,035
We have to celebrate.

581
00:40:13,577 --> 00:40:16,246
To the triumph of Kangsik Sect.

582
00:40:16,330 --> 00:40:18,206
- Salute.
- Salute.

583
00:40:20,459 --> 00:40:23,045
- Kang-sik, what the hell are you doing?
- Salute.

584
00:40:24,338 --> 00:40:26,590
Hey, President Yoo.
Can't you read the room?

585
00:40:27,466 --> 00:40:31,094
Who do you think gave me
the SD card from the dashcam?

586
00:40:35,474 --> 00:40:38,518
Geum Kang-sik, you son of a bitch!
How could you do this to me?

587
00:40:38,602 --> 00:40:39,811
Why are you cussing?

588
00:40:40,562 --> 00:40:45,400
In-gu. I can't spend the rest of my life
getting kicked around by you.

589
00:40:45,484 --> 00:40:47,527
I'm too old for that.

590
00:40:47,611 --> 00:40:50,238
It's time for me to stand on my own feet,
don't you think?

591
00:40:54,284 --> 00:40:55,285
Guys.

592
00:40:58,080 --> 00:41:00,415
Hey, you think you can get away with this?

593
00:41:00,499 --> 00:41:01,792
Hey, Mr. Geum. No, I mean...

594
00:41:01,875 --> 00:41:02,918
It's President Geum now.

595
00:41:03,919 --> 00:41:06,213
It's getting late,
so let's see President Yoo off.

596
00:41:06,296 --> 00:41:07,839
And we can sit down for a drink.

597
00:41:07,923 --> 00:41:09,132
- Yes, sir.
- Have a seat.

598
00:41:09,216 --> 00:41:10,509
Hey, guys, what are you doing?

599
00:41:10,592 --> 00:41:13,387
In-gu is going to a better place.
Let's see him off properly.

600
00:41:13,470 --> 00:41:15,389
Hey. Wait.

601
00:41:20,686 --> 00:41:21,812
Let me just say one thing.

602
00:41:22,729 --> 00:41:23,730
Huh?

603
00:41:35,909 --> 00:41:39,830
I guess my boy Kang-sik
learned a lot from me.

604
00:41:39,913 --> 00:41:41,456
He even knows
how to stab his boss in the back.

605
00:41:43,750 --> 00:41:44,751
Chairman Do.

606
00:41:45,419 --> 00:41:46,962
I've accepted that I'm going out.

607
00:41:48,130 --> 00:41:49,297
But one thing before I do.

608
00:41:49,756 --> 00:41:51,967
A man can have
a glass of champagne, right?

609
00:41:52,050 --> 00:41:53,885
You've lost your mind.

610
00:41:53,969 --> 00:41:56,680
In-gu, what are you trying to pull?

611
00:41:56,763 --> 00:41:58,724
Nothing. I've just got a long trip ahead.

612
00:41:58,807 --> 00:42:01,435
And I'm feeling quite thirsty.
So pour me a glass.

613
00:42:01,518 --> 00:42:02,561
Don't be scared.

614
00:42:04,646 --> 00:42:06,064
Chairman Do.

615
00:42:06,148 --> 00:42:07,899
This kid's a coward.

616
00:42:09,276 --> 00:42:13,280
- Trying to be clever, huh?
- Okay, okay.

617
00:42:14,406 --> 00:42:16,324
President Yoo and I have a history.

618
00:42:16,783 --> 00:42:18,785
A farewell drink is the least I can offer.

619
00:42:20,495 --> 00:42:22,956
There. Goodbye.

620
00:42:41,183 --> 00:42:42,309
Seriously?

621
00:42:48,732 --> 00:42:50,275
Unbelievable.

622
00:43:07,334 --> 00:43:09,503
Hey, don't be scared.

623
00:43:27,187 --> 00:43:31,024
- Boss!
- Don't move. Hey, drop the knife.

624
00:43:32,025 --> 00:43:33,485
Drop the knife.

625
00:43:35,737 --> 00:43:37,280
What are you waiting for? I'll do it!

626
00:43:37,364 --> 00:43:38,949
I'll stab him for real!

627
00:43:39,032 --> 00:43:40,033
- Drop them.
- Drop the knives!

628
00:43:40,117 --> 00:43:41,993
- Drop the knives!
- Come on!

629
00:43:43,787 --> 00:43:45,831
- Hey, Kang-sik.
- Yes, Boss.

630
00:43:45,914 --> 00:43:47,958
- I'll be back soon.
- Yes.

631
00:43:48,041 --> 00:43:49,835
- Make sure you watch your shins.
- Huh?

632
00:43:55,340 --> 00:43:56,675
Go after him! Hurry!

633
00:43:57,843 --> 00:43:59,094
Hey! Get him!

634
00:44:01,138 --> 00:44:03,306
President Yoo never disappoints.

635
00:44:05,225 --> 00:44:08,353
Life's gonna be so boring with him gone.

636
00:44:12,524 --> 00:44:13,525
Get him!

637
00:44:37,132 --> 00:44:39,384
He's getting away! Get him!

638
00:44:48,977 --> 00:44:50,896
- Shit!
- Stop!

639
00:44:53,857 --> 00:44:55,859
Get him!

640
00:44:57,861 --> 00:44:59,321
Geum Kang-sik.

641
00:44:59,404 --> 00:45:01,948
Do Hyeon-tae. Han Gyeong-wook.
You sons of bitches!

642
00:45:06,203 --> 00:45:08,330
Boss, what should we do?

643
00:45:08,413 --> 00:45:11,458
Damn it. Even if he runs,
he's still on the island.

644
00:45:11,541 --> 00:45:14,377
What can he do without a single penny?

645
00:45:16,087 --> 00:45:17,547
Get some guys to guard the terminal.

646
00:45:18,173 --> 00:45:19,925
Search every place he could've gone.

647
00:45:20,008 --> 00:45:21,259
Yes, Boss.

648
00:45:22,385 --> 00:45:25,138
ORAN CHINESE RESTAURANT

649
00:45:31,937 --> 00:45:33,021
O-ran.

650
00:45:33,813 --> 00:45:35,982
Are you planning on going out again today?

651
00:45:36,066 --> 00:45:37,067
Why?

652
00:45:37,567 --> 00:45:38,902
Well, the thing is...

653
00:45:38,985 --> 00:45:41,738
We're fully booked today.

654
00:45:42,572 --> 00:45:44,366
Never mind. We can handle it.

655
00:45:44,449 --> 00:45:45,492
Forget it!

656
00:45:45,784 --> 00:45:47,202
Stop beating around the bush.

657
00:45:48,662 --> 00:45:51,706
This has gone too far, hasn't it?

658
00:45:51,790 --> 00:45:55,168
After Jeong left,
you're always out and about.

659
00:45:55,252 --> 00:45:58,755
Do you have any idea
how much work that is for Kim and me?

660
00:45:58,838 --> 00:46:02,801
Do I have to spend my twilight years
walking on eggshells around my daughter?

661
00:46:05,428 --> 00:46:07,806
Okay, I get it.

662
00:46:08,139 --> 00:46:09,808
I'll stick around for today.

663
00:46:09,891 --> 00:46:12,644
From opening until closing,
I'll take care of everything myself.

664
00:46:12,727 --> 00:46:15,647
You two, don't even lift a finger today.

665
00:46:15,730 --> 00:46:19,025
- Just sit around and rest.
- Really? You mean it?

666
00:46:19,150 --> 00:46:20,235
Of course I do.

667
00:46:20,318 --> 00:46:22,279
I wasn't planning on
going out today anyway.

668
00:46:22,362 --> 00:46:24,197
You two should just rest today.

669
00:46:31,705 --> 00:46:33,665
Hold on, this is so sudden.

670
00:46:33,748 --> 00:46:34,958
I'll have a cup of coffee first.

671
00:46:35,041 --> 00:46:36,459
Sit down.

672
00:46:36,543 --> 00:46:38,795
Why are you being so quick?
It's not like you.

673
00:46:38,878 --> 00:46:41,089
I'll get it. Yes.

674
00:46:43,425 --> 00:46:45,510
- Just a sec.
- Are you that happy?

675
00:46:48,555 --> 00:46:50,807
This just in. We have breaking news.

676
00:46:50,890 --> 00:46:54,561
Kim Seon-jung, who was leading the polls
for the Imcheon mayoral election

677
00:46:54,644 --> 00:46:56,688
has just withdrawn from the race.

678
00:46:56,771 --> 00:47:00,984
While Kim cited health reasons
for his withdrawal

679
00:47:01,067 --> 00:47:04,946
his supporters have had
mixed reactions to the sudden news.

680
00:47:05,905 --> 00:47:10,493
I'd like to once again
apologize to my supporters.

681
00:47:10,577 --> 00:47:16,207
And I'd like to thank them
for the support they've sent me.

682
00:47:18,209 --> 00:47:20,337
Did you look into it like I asked you to?

683
00:47:20,420 --> 00:47:23,298
About that martial arts master
and the guys in the masks.

684
00:47:24,674 --> 00:47:27,469
I put the cops on it,
and they're searching high and low.

685
00:47:27,552 --> 00:47:30,472
And about the orphanage employee
you asked me to look into.

686
00:47:30,555 --> 00:47:32,390
I have a few of my guys watching him.

687
00:47:32,474 --> 00:47:34,059
So if...

688
00:47:34,142 --> 00:47:37,604
If anyone approaches him,
we'll get a call.

689
00:47:37,687 --> 00:47:40,231
Good job, good job.
That's the Mr. Geum I know.

690
00:47:40,315 --> 00:47:41,733
I mean, President Geum.

691
00:47:41,816 --> 00:47:43,526
You and I are totally in sync.

692
00:47:44,319 --> 00:47:45,612
I knew it would be like this.

693
00:47:45,695 --> 00:47:47,072
Eat up. Get some of that meat.

694
00:47:55,205 --> 00:47:56,498
Stomp harder.

695
00:47:57,082 --> 00:47:58,875
The stain here isn't coming out at all.

696
00:47:59,584 --> 00:48:00,794
This is slavery.

697
00:48:01,628 --> 00:48:04,089
You're supposed to wash
blankets in a machine.

698
00:48:04,172 --> 00:48:05,715
Why are we washing them like this?

699
00:48:05,799 --> 00:48:07,258
Nam-il, stomp on the end a little more.

700
00:48:10,345 --> 00:48:13,848
Goodness.
You're all working so hard this morning.

701
00:48:13,932 --> 00:48:15,058
Ah, Prosecutor Gang.

702
00:48:15,141 --> 00:48:17,102
I heard you're taking the boat back
to the office today.

703
00:48:17,185 --> 00:48:19,479
Yes. But that's in the evening.

704
00:48:19,979 --> 00:48:22,857
Well, don't be a stranger, okay?

705
00:48:22,941 --> 00:48:24,192
Of course not.

706
00:48:24,275 --> 00:48:27,362
I'll take care of some urgent business,
and then I'll be right back.

707
00:48:27,445 --> 00:48:28,446
All right.

708
00:48:29,989 --> 00:48:31,783
- Are you busy?
- Huh?

709
00:48:32,158 --> 00:48:34,828
There's something I need to
talk to you about before I leave.

710
00:48:36,287 --> 00:48:38,248
Oh, sure. We can talk here.

711
00:48:43,002 --> 00:48:45,046
No, it's important.
Let's go to a cafe to talk.

712
00:48:45,130 --> 00:48:47,006
I'll be waiting downstairs. Come on out.

713
00:48:47,090 --> 00:48:48,550
I'm just stepping out for a bit.

714
00:48:49,259 --> 00:48:50,260
Okay.

715
00:48:54,514 --> 00:48:55,890
What's going on?

716
00:48:56,724 --> 00:48:58,143
What's going on between you two?

717
00:48:58,226 --> 00:49:00,478
She wants to talk to me
about something important at a cafe.

718
00:49:00,562 --> 00:49:02,897
See? What did I tell you?

719
00:49:03,857 --> 00:49:06,484
I'm telling you,
there was something in her eyes.

720
00:49:06,568 --> 00:49:07,944
It's not like that.

721
00:49:08,027 --> 00:49:10,822
I wonder why she wants to see me.

722
00:49:11,156 --> 00:49:13,032
Whoa, wait a second.

723
00:49:17,036 --> 00:49:19,289
- You can't go like that.
- He's right.

724
00:49:19,372 --> 00:49:20,832
A woman asked you out on a date.

725
00:49:20,915 --> 00:49:23,501
- You can't go looking like that.
- It's not a date.

726
00:49:23,960 --> 00:49:25,044
It's just...

727
00:50:12,383 --> 00:50:13,426
Nam-il said...

728
00:50:16,179 --> 00:50:17,847
that it was cold,
so I should wear warm clothes.

729
00:50:17,931 --> 00:50:19,182
He even gave me this cap.

730
00:50:20,141 --> 00:50:22,060
- It looks weird, right?
- No.

731
00:50:24,187 --> 00:50:25,188
It's cute, actually.

732
00:50:27,273 --> 00:50:28,525
Let's go.

733
00:50:36,950 --> 00:50:39,702
- Director!
- O-ran.

734
00:50:39,786 --> 00:50:42,038
What happened? How could he resign?

735
00:50:42,121 --> 00:50:43,122
What should I do?

736
00:50:43,581 --> 00:50:45,333
My goodness.

737
00:50:46,584 --> 00:50:47,669
It's all my fault.

738
00:50:48,503 --> 00:50:51,798
I had no idea they'd bribed
one of our own staff.

739
00:50:51,881 --> 00:50:54,551
He told me that Chairman Do was suspicious

740
00:50:54,634 --> 00:50:57,262
and that I shouldn't
take anything from him.

741
00:50:58,429 --> 00:51:01,516
- I was so stupid.
- No, hey.

742
00:51:01,599 --> 00:51:03,142
Please calm down, Director.

743
00:51:06,104 --> 00:51:07,647
I can't just sit here.

744
00:51:08,106 --> 00:51:10,608
O-ran, I'm sorry, but I have to go now.

745
00:51:10,692 --> 00:51:11,776
I'll explain later.

746
00:51:11,859 --> 00:51:14,279
Wait, no.
What are you going to do out there?

747
00:51:14,404 --> 00:51:16,990
That employee and I worked together
for over ten years.

748
00:51:17,073 --> 00:51:20,159
If I go and persuade him,
he'll confess that he did it.

749
00:51:20,243 --> 00:51:23,496
He'll come clean and say
my husband had nothing to do with it.

750
00:51:23,580 --> 00:51:26,457
These people bribed your employee
to blackmail your husband.

751
00:51:26,541 --> 00:51:28,293
They're no ordinary guys.

752
00:51:28,376 --> 00:51:30,295
I'll try to figure something out,

753
00:51:30,378 --> 00:51:32,672
so for now, just wait here.

754
00:51:33,506 --> 00:51:35,425
I can't just wait.

755
00:51:35,800 --> 00:51:39,262
If I wait too long,
he can't take back his resignation.

756
00:51:40,054 --> 00:51:41,306
It's my fault.

757
00:51:41,389 --> 00:51:44,058
I can't let him
give up the election like this.

758
00:51:44,142 --> 00:51:45,643
- O-ran, I have to go.
- No.

759
00:51:45,727 --> 00:51:47,895
- I have to do something.
- Then let me come with you.

760
00:51:49,397 --> 00:51:52,150
- You'll come with me?
- It's better than you going alone.

761
00:51:52,233 --> 00:51:53,610
Let me come with you.

762
00:52:05,246 --> 00:52:06,247
Beom-ryong.

763
00:52:11,544 --> 00:52:12,545
Beom-ryong.

764
00:52:17,216 --> 00:52:18,217
I'm sorry.

765
00:52:18,301 --> 00:52:19,927
I was zoning out for a second.

766
00:52:21,638 --> 00:52:24,223
I know yesterday's visit didn't go well.

767
00:52:24,307 --> 00:52:26,225
But don't let it affect your work.

768
00:52:26,309 --> 00:52:27,810
How do you know about that?

769
00:52:27,894 --> 00:52:30,647
You didn't look like you were
heading to HQ, so I looked into it.

770
00:52:31,564 --> 00:52:33,775
What? Did seeing Hwang affect you?

771
00:52:33,858 --> 00:52:37,695
Do you feel uneasy teaming up
with your sworn enemy, an NIS agent?

772
00:52:38,321 --> 00:52:40,782
Gosh, I couldn't even bring it up.

773
00:52:41,783 --> 00:52:45,328
My boss thinks
I'm working with Prosecutor Gang.

774
00:52:45,411 --> 00:52:47,914
Oh, man.

775
00:52:49,707 --> 00:52:52,835
Well, I guess Chairman Hwang
considers us enemies.

776
00:52:52,919 --> 00:52:55,546
So it would be hard
to just tell him the truth.

777
00:52:55,630 --> 00:52:58,007
But then, you could tell him

778
00:52:58,091 --> 00:53:00,009
we're comrades
who took down Yoo In-gu together.

779
00:53:01,010 --> 00:53:04,097
I have no idea
how to explain this situation.

780
00:53:04,180 --> 00:53:06,057
Jeong Ho-myeong and I

781
00:53:06,140 --> 00:53:08,601
could be back at each other's throats
at any moment.

782
00:53:09,143 --> 00:53:10,978
Man, don't get all scary all of a sudden.

783
00:53:11,062 --> 00:53:13,356
I'm telling you.
He's only a dick when he talks.

784
00:53:13,439 --> 00:53:14,899
Don't be ridiculous.

785
00:53:14,982 --> 00:53:16,943
Man, you're so clueless.

786
00:53:17,819 --> 00:53:20,863
Do you have any idea how considerate
Ho-myeong is being of you?

787
00:53:23,116 --> 00:53:25,827
- Considerate?
- Good grief.

788
00:53:26,828 --> 00:53:29,163
He told me not to say anything,
but you leave me no choice.

789
00:53:39,090 --> 00:53:43,386
Even with a new boss,
our job is always the same.

790
00:53:43,469 --> 00:53:46,889
Every day, it's watching, beating,
and threatening people.

791
00:53:48,850 --> 00:53:50,643
I'm so sick of it.

792
00:53:50,727 --> 00:53:52,270
You got that right.

793
00:53:52,353 --> 00:53:56,149
- And you were even promoted.
- Tell me about it.

794
00:54:22,258 --> 00:54:23,509
What's this?

795
00:54:25,219 --> 00:54:27,305
- Yeah?
- Kim Seon-jung's wife showed up.

796
00:54:27,388 --> 00:54:29,515
- What?
- But another woman came with her.

797
00:54:29,599 --> 00:54:30,600
Remember her?

798
00:54:30,683 --> 00:54:33,102
The one who came
to Kim Seon-jung's house in a van.

799
00:54:34,020 --> 00:54:36,606
You know, with the frying pan!

800
00:54:36,689 --> 00:54:38,524
- Yeah.
- What should we do?

801
00:54:40,234 --> 00:54:42,779
Hey, just stand by for now.
It's broad daylight.

802
00:54:42,862 --> 00:54:45,031
There are too many eyes around.
Just stand by.

803
00:54:46,073 --> 00:54:50,161
Let me think. We need a cleanup crew.

804
00:55:05,885 --> 00:55:08,596
YEONGSEON POLICE SUBSTATION

805
00:55:16,979 --> 00:55:18,481
Yes, Boss.

806
00:55:18,564 --> 00:55:21,025
Hey, Sergeant Kim. You got a minute?

807
00:55:21,108 --> 00:55:23,903
- How about a patrol?
- A patrol?

808
00:55:23,986 --> 00:55:25,488
You mean right now?

809
00:55:25,571 --> 00:55:28,991
Yeah. Quick and clean, just like always.

810
00:55:29,408 --> 00:55:32,912
- You know the drill.
- Quick and clean. Send the address.

811
00:55:32,995 --> 00:55:34,372
Yes, Boss.

812
00:55:47,593 --> 00:55:48,719
Jesus Christ.

813
00:55:56,602 --> 00:55:58,521
- What are you doing here?
- What do you think?

814
00:55:59,730 --> 00:56:00,982
- Go.
- What?

815
00:56:01,065 --> 00:56:04,986
You go watch the CCTV feed.
I'll handle things here.

816
00:56:26,257 --> 00:56:27,925
I heard everything from Mr. Jo.

817
00:56:28,718 --> 00:56:29,969
That Mi-kyung...

818
00:56:31,929 --> 00:56:33,055
is the woman from the van.

819
00:56:34,473 --> 00:56:37,727
- We don't know for sure yet.
- Whatever.

820
00:56:39,312 --> 00:56:40,938
You said you saw her face
at Yeongseon Port.

821
00:56:41,480 --> 00:56:42,565
This is ridiculous.

822
00:56:42,648 --> 00:56:45,109
How is it considerate
to leave me out of the operation?

823
00:56:46,235 --> 00:56:48,571
You think I'm stupid enough
to let something like this break me?

824
00:56:50,114 --> 00:56:53,159
- Yeah, I do.
- You bastard.

825
00:56:57,204 --> 00:56:59,081
I wasn't exactly worried about you.

826
00:56:59,165 --> 00:57:02,752
I just needed to look into it
calmly and objectively.

827
00:57:02,835 --> 00:57:04,003
So you don't need to thank me.

828
00:57:08,299 --> 00:57:09,759
From now on, you tell me everything.

829
00:57:10,718 --> 00:57:13,387
We're supposed to be temporary allies.
No more secrets.

830
00:57:16,474 --> 00:57:18,017
Answer me.

831
00:57:24,440 --> 00:57:27,652
- Is it time for the patrol already?
- Let's follow them and find out.

832
00:57:35,159 --> 00:57:36,619
So...

833
00:57:38,204 --> 00:57:40,623
What was it that you wanted to discuss?

834
00:57:44,627 --> 00:57:47,880
I wasn't sure if I should tell you.

835
00:57:48,464 --> 00:57:51,509
Because for you,
this could be a huge deal.

836
00:57:53,260 --> 00:57:54,679
But I thought you should know.

837
00:57:56,389 --> 00:57:58,099
You do have a point.

838
00:57:59,100 --> 00:58:01,852
If it's hard to talk about,
you can tell me later.

839
00:58:01,936 --> 00:58:03,771
Procrastinating just isn't in my books.

840
00:58:05,564 --> 00:58:06,565
Je-sun.

841
00:58:06,649 --> 00:58:08,484
Oh, just a second. This is my first time.

842
00:58:08,567 --> 00:58:10,152
Well, not my first time, but...

843
00:58:11,153 --> 00:58:15,700
I just need a moment to process this.
It's all so sudden.

844
00:58:16,534 --> 00:58:18,577
But no matter what your lost past holds

845
00:58:18,661 --> 00:58:22,206
you're ready to accept it, aren't you?

846
00:58:22,289 --> 00:58:23,290
Huh?

847
00:58:24,917 --> 00:58:26,919
Oh, yeah, that's right.
But why do you ask?

848
00:58:29,422 --> 00:58:31,173
Based on the circumstances

849
00:58:32,633 --> 00:58:34,593
it appears that in the past

850
00:58:34,677 --> 00:58:37,013
you were a special agent from North Korea.

851
00:58:38,848 --> 00:58:39,890
What?

852
00:58:44,603 --> 00:58:46,272
Here, read this article.

853
00:58:47,273 --> 00:58:49,275
An NIS agent and a North Korean agent

854
00:58:49,358 --> 00:58:53,029
went missing during
a rendezvous on a ferry.

855
00:58:53,112 --> 00:58:55,156
But take a look at the date
of the article.

856
00:58:55,239 --> 00:58:57,908
It matches up with the time
you were rescued at sea.

857
00:58:58,909 --> 00:59:00,453
And most importantly...

858
00:59:02,705 --> 00:59:04,915
The dress the woman
is wearing in this photo.

859
00:59:04,999 --> 00:59:06,459
Doesn't it look familiar?

860
00:59:07,460 --> 00:59:10,671
It's the dress you showed me yesterday.

861
00:59:11,630 --> 00:59:13,340
Come on, that's ridiculous.

862
00:59:14,425 --> 00:59:17,678
No way. Me, a spy?

863
00:59:18,554 --> 00:59:20,473
I mean, maybe an NIS agent.

864
00:59:20,556 --> 00:59:22,099
I don't even have a North Korean accent.

865
00:59:22,183 --> 00:59:24,852
My ID says Bong Je-sun, too.
This is ridiculous.

866
00:59:24,935 --> 00:59:27,688
Many spies who've been in the South
for a long time don't have an accent.

867
00:59:28,314 --> 00:59:31,067
And if you were an NIS Agent?

868
00:59:31,192 --> 00:59:34,153
The NIS would have reached out
the moment you ran a background check.

869
00:59:34,236 --> 00:59:37,364
But no matter how many times
you ran the check,

870
00:59:37,448 --> 00:59:39,450
you never found
any family or acquaintances.

871
00:59:40,910 --> 00:59:45,664
As you can see,
all of this evidence points to one thing.

872
00:59:46,749 --> 00:59:47,875
I'm certain of it.

873
00:59:47,958 --> 00:59:49,418
You're a North Korean agent.

874
00:59:51,837 --> 00:59:53,714
So I was alone from the start.

875
00:59:55,424 --> 00:59:57,551
I really have no family.

876
00:59:59,053 --> 01:00:01,722
- Je-sun, I get this is confusing.
- No.

877
01:00:03,432 --> 01:00:05,226
I'm just Bong Je-sun.

878
01:00:06,227 --> 01:00:07,770
Je-sun.

879
01:00:14,401 --> 01:00:16,403
- Hey, they're here. Get ready.
- Yeah. Let's go.

880
01:00:20,991 --> 01:00:22,409
YEONGSEON FOOD

881
01:00:28,207 --> 01:00:31,043
- Aren't those from Heaven Capital?
- They are.

882
01:00:31,710 --> 01:00:33,170
Hey, don't you think
we should do something?

883
01:00:33,254 --> 01:00:35,881
They look like they're about to
cause some serious trouble.

884
01:00:38,676 --> 01:00:40,094
Hey, now.

885
01:00:40,177 --> 01:00:42,012
What are you doing?

886
01:00:42,096 --> 01:00:44,265
You want me to just sit and watch?

887
01:00:44,348 --> 01:00:45,891
Hey, did you forget
Prosecutor Gang's orders?

888
01:00:45,975 --> 01:00:47,685
We're just here to do surveillance.

889
01:00:47,768 --> 01:00:50,020
Let's not get involved
and make things worse.

890
01:00:50,104 --> 01:00:51,355
We should just wait.

891
01:00:51,438 --> 01:00:54,650
If a report comes in,
we can just clean up the mess.

892
01:00:57,570 --> 01:00:59,488
I'll go check it out. You wait here.

893
01:01:01,782 --> 01:01:04,577
You think you can handle it alone?
I'm going with you.

894
01:01:04,827 --> 01:01:07,496
Hey, she knows what you look like.
Just wait here.

895
01:01:28,350 --> 01:01:31,103
This is 29 Samil-ro.
We need backup for a missing six-year-old.

896
01:01:31,187 --> 01:01:32,605
We're the closest unit.

897
01:01:34,148 --> 01:01:35,149
What do we do?

898
01:01:37,151 --> 01:01:39,486
Nothing's going on here.

899
01:01:44,825 --> 01:01:46,994
- Let's go for now.
- Yeah, let's go.

900
01:01:47,077 --> 01:01:48,078
Let's go.

901
01:01:56,545 --> 01:01:57,963
Please leave.

902
01:01:58,047 --> 01:01:59,173
I have nothing to say.

903
01:01:59,256 --> 01:02:00,549
Mr. Park!

904
01:02:02,301 --> 01:02:04,929
If something's gone wrong,
you have to make it right.

905
01:02:05,012 --> 01:02:08,057
Didn't you see that my husband
resigned today because of you?

906
01:02:08,682 --> 01:02:10,267
Please, stop.

907
01:02:10,351 --> 01:02:12,519
If you keep this up,
I'll be the one who gets hurt.

908
01:02:13,520 --> 01:02:17,441
Hurt? Please tell me.
Are you being threatened?

909
01:02:21,779 --> 01:02:23,948
Who are you people?

910
01:02:25,449 --> 01:02:26,867
What are you doing? Get them out of here.

911
01:02:26,951 --> 01:02:28,244
- What are you waiting for?
- Oh, goodness.

912
01:02:28,327 --> 01:02:31,789
- Hey, who are you?
- Why are you doing this?

913
01:02:32,831 --> 01:02:34,792
- Let go of me!
- Hey, what are you doing?

914
01:02:34,875 --> 01:02:36,877
- Let go of me!
- You don't have to do this.

915
01:02:37,461 --> 01:02:39,046
Oh no!

916
01:02:39,129 --> 01:02:40,339
I said let me go!

917
01:02:40,422 --> 01:02:43,968
You can't even drag a woman out? Move!

918
01:02:44,051 --> 01:02:45,803
Please, spare my life. Please.

919
01:02:45,886 --> 01:02:47,638
Chang-su,
if you just help me out this once

920
01:02:47,721 --> 01:02:49,014
I can get back on my feet again.

921
01:02:49,098 --> 01:02:51,433
Word gets around fast in this business.

922
01:02:51,517 --> 01:02:53,686
They say you lost the drugs
and went broke.

923
01:02:53,769 --> 01:02:55,521
And all your backers dropped you.

924
01:02:55,604 --> 01:02:56,897
So why would I help you out?

925
01:02:56,981 --> 01:02:58,774
Hey, you disloyal bastard.
You can't do this to me.

926
01:02:58,857 --> 01:03:00,109
Would you look at this?

927
01:03:00,192 --> 01:03:04,029
You stabbed your own boss in the back.
You want to talk about loyalty?

928
01:03:04,113 --> 01:03:05,447
Don't drag me into your mess.

929
01:03:05,531 --> 01:03:07,866
- Crawl into a hole and stay put.
- What?

930
01:03:08,951 --> 01:03:10,202
Hey!

931
01:03:24,216 --> 01:03:27,219
Martial arts master?
And is that Gang Yeong-ae?

932
01:03:27,303 --> 01:03:28,679
Why are they still alive?

933
01:03:32,433 --> 01:03:34,101
They've been working together?

934
01:03:37,604 --> 01:03:41,483
I may be going down,
but I'm taking you with me.

935
01:04:05,090 --> 01:04:06,175
Je-sun!

936
01:04:12,556 --> 01:04:14,224
Let me go!

937
01:04:14,433 --> 01:04:15,934
Please! Let me go!

938
01:04:23,359 --> 01:04:24,401
Get off me!

939
01:04:29,323 --> 01:04:30,866
Come here.

940
01:04:30,949 --> 01:04:33,452
Let's go. Have you lost your mind?

941
01:04:49,802 --> 01:04:50,803
Oh no!

942
01:05:11,156 --> 01:05:13,700
SPECIAL THANKS TO
KIM SANG-KYUNG AND KWON YUL

943
01:05:28,465 --> 01:05:30,592
- Are you sure about this?
- I'm going to come clean.

944
01:05:30,676 --> 01:05:32,761
I was a black ops agent for the NIS.

945
01:05:32,845 --> 01:05:34,680
So you've been lying to me for 10 years.

946
01:05:34,763 --> 01:05:37,307
They are a force to be reckoned with.

947
01:05:37,391 --> 01:05:39,935
They're not the kind of people
a patrol officer like you can handle.

948
01:05:40,018 --> 01:05:42,438
You have no right to tell me what to do.

949
01:05:42,521 --> 01:05:45,566
- What do you think of my uncle?
- I think you're a really good person.

950
01:05:45,649 --> 01:05:47,192
Bulgae is not an amnesiac.

951
01:05:47,276 --> 01:05:49,403
He's Bulgae, a human weapon
trained by North Korea.

952
01:05:49,486 --> 01:05:52,448
- I really don't remember anything.
- He's definitely up to something.

953
01:05:52,531 --> 01:05:54,616
To me, it seemed like
he really didn't remember anything.

954
01:05:54,700 --> 01:05:56,160
Drop the act, you goddamn spy.

955
01:05:56,243 --> 01:05:59,204
He's Bulgae, not Bong Je-sun.
